                        <h4>
                            Week 3-4                                                        </h4>
                        <h5><a href='http://localhost:3032/hci401/schedule'>
                            Back to HCI401 Schedule                        </a></h5>
                    </header>
                    <div class="content">
                                                <h4><a href="https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/1yDi89XGfmRav2NdB9xI0VqJ6vVXL8eMAAQ4uXPUnQvU/edit?usp=sharing"><i class='icon-th-list icon-large'></i>   Know the User</a></h4>

<h4><a href="../slides/requirementsgathering"><i class='icon-th-list icon-large'></i>   Requirements Gathering</a></h4>

<h4><a href="http://husk.eecs.berkeley.edu/courses/cs160-sp11/images/2/24/Cs160-sp11-05.pdf"><i class='icon-th-list icon-large'></i>   Task Analysis &amp; Contextual Inquiry</a></h4>

<h4><a href="https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/1tb_qmUnQ9442zXUV0NJmfd9sq3roEzstBtll6DOT1N0/edit?usp=sharing"><i class='icon-th-list icon-large'></i>   Interaction Design</a></h4>

<ul>
<li>Wiley <a href="http://www.wiley.com/legacy/wileychi/interactiondesign/pdf/ID_ch6.pdf">Chapter</a> on Interaction Design</li>
<li>BART Design (BART ui <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=V4_ZzaIe2Lc&amp;feature=BFa&amp;list=PL13B810A5F19581D0&amp;lf=mh_lolz">video1</a>, <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4ihTOH7_FZY&amp;feature=BFa&amp;list=PL13B810A5F19581D0&amp;lf=mh_lolz">video2</a>, <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Kyl2g11KSqc">video3</a>,  <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=M79xjOtVP4o&amp;feature=BFa&amp;list=PL13B810A5F19581D0&amp;lf=mh_lolz">redesigned</a>, <a href="http://williamclark.prosite.com/43819/395766/interaction-design/the-bart-kiosk-redux">redesigned2</a>)</li>
<li>Real-world exercise in Contextual Inquiry (<a href="http://www.adamatorres.com/gallery-project/?page_id=106">Photodev</a>) by <a href="http://www.adamatorres.com/gallery-project/?page_id=106">Adam Torres</a></li>
<li>The Paradox of Choice (<a href="http://www.smashingmagazine.com/2011/11/28/easier-is-better-than-better/">Smashing</a>)</li>
<li>Barry Schwartz: The Paradox of Choice <a href="http://www.ted.com/talks/barry_schwartz_on_the_paradox_of_choice.html?utm_source=email&amp;source=email&amp;utm_medium=social&amp;utm_campaign=ios-share">(TED video)</a></li>
<li>Google <a href="http://www.google.com/about/corporate/company/tenthings.html">Mission</a> statement (Google)</li>
<li>David Kelley: <a href="http://www.ted.com/talks/lang/eng/david_kelley_on_human_centered_design.html">IDEO</a> (TED)</li>
<li>Psychological Usability <a href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheet/ccc?key=0An-LJr2fswPHdGRDMUdQU3BKQmgteXd2UVcwVjhtb3c&amp;hl=en_US#gid=0">Heuristics</a> (UX Mag, _ _<a href="http://uxmag.com/contributors/jordi-s%C3%A1nchez" title="View user profile.">Jordi Sánchez</a>)</li>
<li>The $300m <a href="http://www.uie.com/brainsparks/2011/10/17/the-back-story-for-the-300-million-button/">button</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.alistapart.com/articles/personality-in-design/">Personality in Design</a> (<a href="http://www.alistapart.com/authors/w/awalter">Aarron Walter</a>, UX Lead at MailChimp) (<a href="http://popchartlab.com/collections/prints/products/the-insanely-great-history-of-apple">PopChart</a> faq)</li>
<li><a href="http://www.smashingmagazine.com/2012/02/24/a-fun-approach-to-creating-more-successful-websites/">Fun in Design</a> (Smashing Magazine, Jeremy Girard)</li>
<li><a href="http://startupclass.samaltman.com/courses/lec07/">How to Build Products that Users Love</a> (Sam Altman)</li>
<li>Whither <a href="http://www.fastcodesign.com/1670760/will-apples-tacky-software-design-philosophy-cause-a-revolt">Skeuomorphic Design</a> (FastCompany)</li>
<li>Microsoft's <a href="http://www.fastcodesign.com/1670705/microsoft-new-design-strategy#1">biggest gamble</a> (FastCompany)</li>
<li>Tim Brown: Designers - Think Big <a href="http://www.ted.com/talks/tim_brown_urges_designers_to_think_big.html">(TED2009)</a></li>
</ul>
